type":"inlineCode","value":"dot","position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":1},"end":{"line":60,"column":1}},"key":"ev06davLTM"},{"type":"text","value":" is handled. If you encounter issues, try the following command instead:","position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":1},"end":{"line":60,"column":1}},"key":"G3JewP3Xbt"}],"key":"ROVUkWbzvM"},{"type":"code","lang":"bash","value":"pixi run snakemake --dag | pixi run dot -Tpng > fig/dag.png","position":{"start":{"line":62,"column":1},"end":{"line":63,"column":1}},"key":"HTNk7akC6M"}],"key":"blqooUpgcL"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1},"end":{"line":66,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"or you can run:","position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1},"end":{"line":66,"column":1}},"key":"yBgilbkqbx"}],"key":"ker4IY6obX"},{"type":"code","lang":"bash","value":"pixi run dot -C\npixi run snakemake --dag | pixi run dot -Tpng > fig/dag.png","position":{"start":{"line":68,"column":1},"end":{"line":71,"column":1}},"key":"WLO3bIuf4q"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"\n3. Open `fig/dag.png`. It should look like the following image. Notice how the branches for each dataset are parallel.\n\n![DAG Visualization](fig/dag.png)\n\n```{admonition} Challenge: Identifying the Bottleneck\n:class: warning\nLook at your DAG. If you were to run this on a machine with only **1 core**, how many steps would it take? If you had **4 cores**, how would the timing change?\n\n```{dropdown} Solution\nWith 1 core, Snakemake runs every job sequentially. With 4 cores, Snakemake can run all four `skim_data` jobs simultaneously, significantly reducing the \"Wall Clock\" time of your analysis. This is the power of a DAG-based system!","position":{"start":{"line":72,"column":1},"end":{"line":84,"column":1}},"key":"taub2b1Y4D"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"\n```{note}\n### Rule Graph vs. File Graph\n\nIf you have 1,000 samples, the `--dag` command will produce a giant PDF with 1,000 boxes, which is unreadable. To see a simplified version that only shows how the rules connect (ignoring the individual samples), use:\n\n```bash\npixi run snakemake --rulegraph | dot -Tpng > fig/rulegraph.png","position":{"start":{"line":85,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"key":"h9ycstDLmd"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":1},"end":{"line":96,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This is often much more useful for complex HEP analyses to ensure the logic is correct.","position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":1},"end":{"line":96,"column":1}},"key":"rBnxyDgEpz"}],"key":"CY2Z9dt9VD"},{"type":"image","url":"/rulegraph-9d073505a93f31041d5cb61534ee4a21.png","alt":"Rule Graph Visualization","position":{"start":{"line":98,"column":1},"end":{"line":98,"column":1}},"key":"TsQ5DVPids","urlSource":"fig/rulegraph.png"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"\n## The Dry-Run: \"Look Before You Leap\"\n\nBefore you submit 1,000 jobs to a cluster, you should always perform a **Dry-Run**. This tells Snakemake to calculate the DAG and print the execution plan without actually running any commands.\n\n```bash\npixi run snakemake -n","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1},"end":{"line":107,"column":1}},"key":"Sxqe8pEEqJ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":109,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you want more detail (like seeing the actual shell commands that will be executed), use:","position":{"start":{"line":109,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"key":"R25MUrlqZ0"}],"key":"KetcS8Myd1"},{"type":"code","lang":"bash","value":"pixi run snakemake -n -p","position":{"start":{"line":111,"column":1},"end":{"line":113,"column":1}},"key":"r1ZQPxbI7f"},{"type":"details","children":[{"type":"summary","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Did the previous command work?","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"key":"tgyoKD3uT9"}],"key":"Cs30xmBGTh"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you run this command on top of a finished workflow, you should see something like:","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"key":"Gzi1HbfLEX"}],"key":"s2BtJLcXq2"},{"type":"code","lang":"output","value":"Building DAG of jobs...\nNothing to be done (all requested files are present and up to date).","position":{"start":{"line":118,"column":1},"end":{"line":120,"column":1}},"key":"v3lkQaJJEQ"}],"key":"BnwNl6idVM"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":123,"column":1},"end":{"line":123,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This is expected, because all the output files already exist. If you change something in your Snakefile (like adding a new rule or changing an existing one), the dry-run will show you which jobs need to be re-run.","position":{"start":{"line":123,"column":1},"end":{"line":123,"column":1}},"key":"zkZ8KY5f53"}],"key":"WSFzqMqDso"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1},"end":{"line":125,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Alternatively, if you want to see the dry-run or the commands to execute, use:","position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1},"end":{"line":125,"column":1}},"key":"uSDVUFbLco"}],"key":"J6YnmElguR"},{"type":"code","lang":"bash","value":"pixi run snakemake -n -p --forceall","position":{"start":{"line":127,"column":1},"end":{"line":129,"column":1}},"key":"aveoQtjizx"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"\n```{admonition} Keypoints\n:class: important\n- **DAG**: A visual map of your analysis dependencies.\n- **Dry-run (-n)**: Always perform a dry-run to verify the plan before executing.\n- **Rule Graph**: A simplified visualization showing the relationship between rules rather than individual files.","position":{"start":{"line":130,"column":1},"end":{"line":137,"column":1}},"key":"zjaszcXP3s"}],"key":"uL2qkRcCCT"}],"key":"nbAE7UMNGy"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}}}